{{Unreferenced|date=February 2010}} {{Infobox company | name = Norwegian Food Safety Authority | logo = Mattilsynet logo.png | type = [[Government agency]] | foundation = 2003 | founder = | location = [[Oslo]], [[Norway]] | key_people = [[Harald Johannes Gjein]] <small>([[Director General]])</small> | area_served = [[Norway]] | industry = [[Food safety]] | products = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | num_employees = 1,300 (2007) | parent = [[Norwegian Ministry of Agriculture and Food]] | subsid = | homepage = [http://www.mattilsynet.no www.mattilsynet.no] | footnotes = }}
'''Norwegian Food Safety Authority''' ({{lang-no|Mattilsynet}}) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[etat|government agency]] responsible for safe [[food safety|food]] and [[drinking water]], and works within the fields of [[human health|human]], [[plant health|plant]], [[fish health|fish]] and [[animal health]] as well as environmentally friendly production and [[animal ethics|ethically acceptable]] farming of animals and fish {{Citation needed|date=February 2010}}. Other duties are related to [[cosmetics]], [[medicines]] and inspection of [[animal health personnel]].
Main offices are located in [[Oslo]] while there are 63 district and eight regional offices. There are also three national competence centers: [[fish]] and [[seafood]] in [[Bergen]], [[plants]] and [[vegetarian food]]s in [[Ås, Akershus|Ås]], and [[animal]]s and [[carnivore food]] in [[Sandnes]]. The agency was created in 2003 when four government agencies (the States Food Authority, the Fisheries Directories Seafood Control, the States Animal Authority and the [[Norwegian Agricultural Inspection Service]]) were merged with 69 [[municipalities of Norway|municipal]] food authorities.
==References== *{{cite book|title=Review of Fisheries in Oecd Countries 2009: Policies and Summary Statistics|year=2010|publisher=OECD Publishing|isbn=978-9264079748|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Wege8WebVOEC&pg=PA334&dq=Norwegian+Food+Safety+Authority&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Xgb2T4XmDs648gP9u8CaBw&ved=0CEwQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=Norwegian%20Food%20Safety%20Authority&f=false|accessdate=5 July 2012|page=334}}
