{{Infobox scientist | name = Dr Susan Jebb | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = <!--(filename only, i.e. without "File:" prefix)--> | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1964|8|29|df=y}} | birth_place = Bolton | death_date = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD|1964|8|29|df=y}} (death date then birth date)--> | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}--> | other_names = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = | fields = | workplaces = [[University of Oxford]] | patrons = | alma_mater = | thesis_title = <!--(or | thesis1_title = and | thesis2_title = )--> | thesis_url = <!--(or | thesis1_url = and | thesis2_url = )--> | thesis_year = <!--(or | thesis1_year = and | thesis2_year = )--> | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = {{URL|http://www.phc.ox.ac.uk/team/researchers/susan-jebb}} | footnotes = }} '''Susan Ann Jebb''' [[Officer of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (born 29 August 1964) is a [[nutrition]] scientist, and the Professor of Diet and Population Health at the Nuffield Department of Primary Care Health Sciences at the [[University of Oxford]]. She is the UK Government's advisor on [[obesity in the United Kingdom]].
==Early life== She was born Susan Ann Parkinson.{{citation needed|date=February 2016}} She studied at [[Surrey University]] on a course which included a six-month placement in an [[oncology]] research group at [[St Bartholomew's Hospital, London]].<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Watts|first1=Geoff|title=Susan Jebb: nutritionist with a scientific passion about food|journal=[[The Lancet]]|date=6 June 2015|volume=385|issue=9984|page=2245|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(15)61054-6|pmid=26088488}}</ref>
==Career== She is interested in diet and the [[Diet and obesity|effect this has on obesity]].
===Medical Research Council=== She was Head of Nutrition and Health Research at the [[MRC Human Nutrition Research]] in Cambridge.
===University of Oxford=== She chairs the Food Network on the [[Department of Health (United Kingdom)|Department of Health]]'s [[Public Health Responsibility Deal]].<ref>[https://responsibilitydeal.dh.gov.uk/category/food-network/ Food network]</ref>
In 2008 she was awarded the OBE for services to public health.
In 2014 she gave advice on the UK government's outlawing of [[Soft drink|sugary drinks]] for children.
==Personal life== She married in June 1990 in [[Ellesmere, Shropshire]] and has a son born 2001 in Cambridge.
