{{italic title}}
'''''The Hungry Gene''''' is a 2002 book by [[Ellen Ruppel Shell]] in which she tackles the issue of [[obesity]]. It is a [[non-fiction]] journalistic [[book]]. The author devotes multiple chapters of her book to the events that led to the co-discovery of the [[Leptin]] gene in 1994. Based on interviews with the parties involved, she reports that [[Leptin]] was co-discovered at [[Rockefeller University]] by [[Rudolph Leibel]], [[Jeffrey M. Friedman|Jeffrey Friedman]], and members of their laboratories, and explains why Leibel and others were excluded by Friedman in the scientific paper that announced the discovery.

